! conclusion: Single-Focus Amidst Agenda Saturation
  + context: The week agenda contains many TODO, NEXT, WAIT, and SHIP items across ORPM and AOB, but only one item is explicitly marked FOCUS.
  + IF:
    There is exactly one FOCUS item while multiple other tasks remain scheduled, recurring, or deadline-bearing.
  + HOWEVER:
    Several non-FOCUS items still demand attention due to deadlines, dependencies, or institutional expectations.
  + THEN:
    Treat the FOCUS item as the sole candidate for discretionary depth, and constrain all other items to execution at their minimal viable level unless they directly unblock or materially enrich the FOCUS.
  + BECAUSE:
    A single declared focus only functions as such if it is protected from dilution by equally attention-hungry tasks.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Check whether any non-FOCUS items causally unblock or substantially reshape the FOCUS; if so, either promote them or explicitly time-box them to prevent silent priority creep.]


