! conclusion: Close Then Reframe Focus
  + context: The current agenda has one explicit FOCUS item alongside many scheduled tasks that have accumulated partial progress or overrun status.
  + IF:
    A FOCUS item is sufficiently bounded that it can be brought to a defensible stopping point.
  + HOWEVER:
    Multiple overrun items compete as plausible successors and risk pulling attention prematurely.
  + THEN:
    Complete the current FOCUS to a clear "finished enough" artifact, then deliberately select the next FOCUS from the overrun set based on leverage rather than urgency.
  + BECAUSE:
    Focus only compounds value when it reaches closure, producing a reference point that informs the next prioritization rather than fragmenting effort.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define what counts as "done enough" for the current FOCUS, list overrun items with a one-line statement of leverage, and choose the next FOCUS explicitly rather than by drift.]
